  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-9b6fbb7d-7fff-4832-4be6-7bef4bfd087e&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;The proposed white UPVC replacement windows and composite front door, by reason of their materials and appearance, and the thickness of the frames and glazing bars, result in a discordant and incongruous appearance with the host dwelling and the wider terrace that fails to preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the Graham Road and Mapledene Conservation Area. The proposal is, therefore, contrary to policies D1, D3, D4, and HC1 of The London Plan (2021) and policies LP1 and LP3 of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed external wall insulation (EWI) with a white render finish will add 120mm thickness to the facade to the main rear elevation and the outrigger. The additional thickness to the rear of the property will harm the pair that the site forms with No. 18 Gayhurst Road. Overall, the proposed EWI will be viewed as a dominant and incongruous addition to the application property when compared with the rear elevations of the properties within the terrace. The proposal is, therefore, contrary to policies D1, D3, D4, and HC1 of The London Plan (2020) and policies LP1 and LP3 of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
